summary: A concept: after getting the Menagerie Coast, the M9 encounter a bunch of albatrosses. One of them takes a strange shine to...
body: A concept: after getting the Menagerie Coast, the M9 encounter a bunch of albatrosses. One of them takes a strange shine to Fjord, following him around and nuzzling at him with its beak. Fjord remembers Vandrin telling him that albatrosses are the souls of dead sailors, and Molly wasn’t a sailor, but a mollymawk is a kind of albatross, and maybe, just maybe…Fjord waits until he’s sure no one is listening and then whispers to the bird, ‘Molly, is that you?’

summary: I’m again and again amazed at the power of fiction. How words, simple words, describing a world and people that shouldn’t be...
body: I’m again and again amazed at the power of fiction. How words, simple words, describing a world and people that shouldn’t be there, that aren’t there, because they are not real, and yet they are - in some way, and I am amazed at how these words can spark feelings so real, so strong, they bring me to tears, they make my heart clench with fear or jump with joy - nothing more than letters on a page or sounds in the air and yet full of such an incredible power. I hope this will never cease to amaze me.

question: jester + whoever you want for 14?
answer:
14. things you said after you kissed me

“Oh,” Beau says, slightly dazed after Jester finally pulls away. She looks goofy with a bit of Jester’s lipstick smeared on the corner of her mouth. “What was that for?”

“Why does it have to be for something?” Jester rolls her eyes. “It’s not, like, a ‘Good job!’ sticker or a cookie or something.” She pauses to consider. “Actually, cookies shouldn’t have to be for specific stuff, either. They’re just for always, you know?”

“No, I mean—” Beau shakes her head, as if to clear it. She touches a hand to Jester’s cheek. “You’re right, yeah. I just wanted to know the cause, so it could, maybe, happen again?”

Jester leans forward, and kisses her again. Gentler, this time.

Beau is back to looking dazed and goofy.

“I just thought you looked really cute today, that’s all,” Jester answers her question. “But don’t worry. I can kiss you even when you look super gross, if you want.”

“In that case,” says Beau, breaking into a dopey grin, “do I look super gross right now?”

“Super fucking gross,” she lies, and leans in one more time.
